Inspection well concrete module production and processing equipment. Introduction to Zhengzhou well wall brick module equipment:
Zhengzhou Yixin is a professional manufacturer of equipment for concrete inspection well modular bricks, machinery for constructing inspection wells, and machinery for manufacturing well wall modules in China. The company offers production lines ranging from semi-automatic to fully automated systems.
Through years of practice and development, we have now established a reputation for producing high-quality equipment, mainly including hydraulic, mobile, and fully automated inspection well systems along with their accompanying accessories.
Inspection of equipment for the production and processing of concrete modules for inspection wells Zhengzhou: Assembly site for well wall brick module equipment
Inspection well concrete module production and processing equipment. Characteristics and advantages of Zhengzhou well wall brick module equipment:
The Yixin inspection well block brick machine equipment is widely applicable to new types of masonry materials for municipal underground structures such as coal, heating, water, electricity, and gas facilities.
Examples include various inspection wells for drainage and water storage facilities, stormwater inlets, square ditches, septic tanks, small structures, and bridge wing walls.
The advantage of using concrete modules to construct inspection wells is that the modules have grooves on all sides – top, bottom, left, and right – which, when assembled together, form a interlocking chain structure.
The shear resistance of the well wall is significantly better than that of masonry constructed using plain frictional bonding methods.
The module has a hollow structure; when assembled and constructed, the longitudinal holes are interconnected, and the transverse holes also intersect with each other. After the cores of these holes are poured, a cast-in-place concrete mesh structure is formed, which provides secondary reinforcement and waterproofing benefits.
The module is equipped with reinforcement slots both horizontally and vertically; the horizontal reinforcement bars and vertical reinforcement rods enhance the overall strength of the structure accordingly.
In addition, inspection wells and drainage wells constructed using concrete inspection well modules are less prone to collapse, subsidence, or leakage. The mechanical properties of the well wall modules are stable, the installation process is simple, and the formed dimensions are standardized.
The intelligent control system for the concrete inspection well module brick machine is equipped with data input and output devices, as well as a one-touch touch screen LCD display that monitors the entire mechanical operation process. This enables ideal human-machine interaction, automatic material ratio analysis, density control, safety logic management, and a fault diagnosis system.
The mechanical-hydraulic system for the wellbore wall module employs single-cylinder hydraulic technology for transportation, as well as double-cylinder hydraulic technology for transportation.
The independent hydraulic integration station eliminates the impact of host vibrations on the hydraulic system, thereby ensuring the reliability of its operation.
The equipment for manufacturing concrete inspection well module bricks includes a material distribution box, a traveling mold box, and a mold removal mechanism. The mold box rises after the process is completed, and the door of the storage box closes. The automatic conveying pallets are also operated independently by the hydraulic system, which helps to reduce mechanical wear and maintenance requirements.
The concrete inspection well module brick manufacturing equipment uses imported computers and electrical components, as well as seals and hydraulic parts, ensuring the overall stability and reliability of the equipment.
The mechanical vibration platform for the wellbore wall module is constructed using integral sheet steel. The tabletop is precision-cut and assembled without any welding points, allowing the filler box to swing freely and guide its movement, thereby significantly reducing mechanical wear.
Reduce the mold load, combine the packing process with the vibration amplitude in a single step, and utilize an integrated, fully synchronized system that includes both table vibration and mold vibration to ensure optimal compaction results.
The well wall module is excited mechanically, with the amplitude automatically controlled by a computer based on the cost-effectiveness of the materials used. There is no wear-related braking, which extends the service life and reduces costs.
The wellbore wall module features both mechanical automatic control and manual control functions.
Inspection well mold:
Yixin Brick Machine Inspection Well: The surface is constructed using cement blocks.
