The China Children’s Center will organize a series of activities to allow children to experience “high-tech” fun on Children’s Day (June 1st) – Xinhua News Agency
Xinhua News Agency, Beijing, May 20th (Huang Xiaoxi, Zhou Shanshan) Reporters learned from the China National Children’s Center on the 20th that from May 28th to June 1st, around Children’s Day, a series of events are planned to be held, including children’s maker experiences, a children’s visual arts festival, and a parent-child book carnival. These activities aim to allow children to celebrate Children’s Day in the charm of cutting-edge technology.
It is understood that the activities organized by the China Children’s Center during this year’s Children’s Day on June 1st include the “Love Home, Create Cool” Children’s Future Learning Carnival, the first Children’s Visual Arts Festival, the “Bookish Carnival,” and a series of activities related to picture books titled “The Whole Family Loves Reading.”
Li Zhongming, the deputy director of the China National Children’s Center, introduced at the media briefing for the 2016 Children’s Day on June 20th that the “Love Home, Create Cool” Children’s Future Learning Carnival is the main event organized by the China National Children’s Center to celebrate Children’s Day this year.
The event focuses on the organic integration of social innovation with individual creativity within families. By involving children and families in various innovative educational activities, it aims to make innovative practices a cultural element within ordinary households, turning “hands-on learning” into a new way of learning and living for many families.
It is reported that the “Love Home, Create Cool” Children’s Future Learning Carnival includes various cutting-edge technology experiences, such as the “Douguo Maker” workshop, the anniversary celebration of the Lao Niu Children’s Exploration Museum and the “Explore Family Love, Have a Fun Children’s Day” event, the VR public experience program, as well as the “Maker Tribe” interactive workshop, among dozens of other activities.
