Ingredients for the beauty and skin-nourishing soup:
The benefits of white fungus: It has a sweet taste and a neutral nature, and it affects the lung, stomach, and kidney meridians. It is effective in strengthening the essence, nourishing the kidneys, moistening the intestines, benefiting the stomach, replenishing qi, harmonizing the blood, strengthening the heart, nourishing yin, moistening the lungs, promoting the production of body fluids, enhancing physical strength, improving brain function, invigorating the mind, beautifying the skin, making the skin more tender, and prolonging life. It is used to treat conditions such as cough due to lung heat, dry
The effects of peach gum: It has a bitter taste and a neutral nature, and it belongs to the Large Intestine and Bladder meridians.
Benefits: It helps to regulate blood flow, promotes urination, stops diarrhea, relieves pain, and also provides hydration while soothing the intestines. For those who suffer from constipation, consuming more peach gum can be beneficial.
The effects of wolfberry fruits: They are neutral in nature, sweet in taste, and act on the liver and stomach meridians.
Benefits the liver and improves eyesight, nourishes the liver and kidneys, enhances skin fairness and beauty, replenishes vital energy, and slows down the aging process.
The benefits of red dates: They have a sweet taste and a mild nature, and they affect the spleen and stomach meridians. Red dates can help to strengthen the spleen and stomach, replenish qi, generate body fluids, nourish the blood, and calm the mind. Those with weak spleen and stomach function, insufficient qi and blood, or insomnia can benefit from consuming more red dates.
The benefits of longan pulp: It has a sweet taste and a warm nature, and it affects the heart and spleen meridians. It is suitable for those with deficiencies in both the heart and spleen.
Longan pulp can also moisturize the skin and enhance beauty, nourish the blood and soothe the mind, benefit the heart and spleen, strengthen yang and boost energy. It is suitable for people with anemia as well as those who suffer from insomnia.
The effects of lotus seeds: They have a sweet and astringent taste, and a neutral nature. They are associated with the heart, spleen, and kidney meridians.
It helps to soothe the mind and calm the nerves, alleviates palpitations and insomnia, addresses stomach weakness and forgetfulness, relieves irritability and thirst, provides nourishment to replenish deficiencies, and stops involuntary urination and excessive semen discharge.
Therefore, this beauty-enhancing soup is not only a delicious dessert but also beneficial for health!
