Jiangxi will train 10,000 primary school teachers in music, physical education, and art within three years – Xinhua News Agency
Xinhua News Agency, Nanchang, May 22 (Reporter Chen Yushan) Reporters have recently learned from the Jiangxi Provincial Department of Education that in order to strengthen the support for teachers in shortage subjects and achieve balanced development of compulsory education in rural areas, starting from 2016, Jiangxi Province plans to train one qualified music teacher, one art teacher, and one physical education teacher for each primary school in rural areas (townships and below) across the province over a period of three years, totaling 10,000 teachers.
It is understood that the training targets teachers from rural primary schools across Jiangxi Province who are under 45 years of age and have a foundational knowledge or talent in music, art, or physical education. These teachers are also capable of teaching other subjects while incorporating music, art, and physical education into their lessons.
Through training, they will acquire the basic knowledge and teaching skills necessary for teaching music, physical education, and art subjects. Their teaching philosophies and concepts will be updated, and they will learn modern teaching methods. This will enhance their ability to teach these subjects, design educational activities, promote campus culture, and develop personally. As a result, a team of music, physical education, and art teachers with specialized skills and versatility will be established, helping to address the shortage of such educators in rural areas.
To ensure the quality and effectiveness of the training, Jiangxi has also planned to provide training for one teacher each in music, art, and physical education at the primary school level in 100 counties (cities, districts) across the province, totaling 300 trainers. The goal is to comprehensively enhance their abilities in teaching demonstration and leadership, design and organization of educational research activities, delivery of training programs, and establishment of online learning workshops. These trainers will serve as instructors, role models, guides, and supervisors.
