Have you encountered any issues with the required continuing education hours for the initial registration of Level 1 Cost Engineers?
Individuals who register after the deadline must provide proof of continuing education. For late registration, proof of at least 30 hours of continuing education within the past year is required. For re-registration, proof of at least 120 hours of continuing education within the past 4 years is necessary. Additionally, for each full year since the last registration, proof of at least 30 hours of continuing education must be provided.
Cost Engineering Professional Continuing Education Fee Standards
Cost engineers participating in online continuing education must pay the tuition fees to the respective management institutions when registering. The general standard is as follows: The cost for 30 hours of compulsory courses is 300 yuan per person per year (including the unified continuing education textbooks).
The cost for a 30-hour elective course is 300 yuan per person per year.
The cost for 30 hours of compulsory courses and 30 hours of elective courses is 600 yuan per person per year (including the unified textbooks for continuing education).
(1) Participate in the online continuing education programs for registered cost engineers organized by the China Construction Cost Association or the provincial and departmental management authorities. The number of study hours is calculated based on the time recorded in the online learning materials.
(II) Participation in centralized face-to-face training for certified cost engineers organized by the China Construction Cost Association or provincial and departmental management agencies, as well as various types of training courses and seminars, can earn 4 academic hours for each half-day of attendance.
(III) Participation in continuing education courses organized by the China Construction Cost Association, as well as provincial and departmental organizations for cost engineers and cost estimators; 10 academic hours can be recognized for each half-day of attendance.
(IV) Participation in research projects conducted by the China Price Association or provincial authorities, the development of industry standards, and the compilation of teaching materials is recognized as 30 academic hours per year for each project.
(VI) Participation in the compilation of textbooks for the national Cost Engineer Practice Qualification Examination, as well as in the process of setting exam questions, reviewing them, and grading papers, is eligible to earn 30 academic hours per year.
(VII) Papers and works related to engineering cost that are personally authored and publicly published (as evidenced by an official publication number).
For published works, 12 academic hours are recognized for every 10,000 words.
For papers published in national-level journals, 8 academic hours are recognized for every thousand words; for papers published in provincial-level journals, 5 academic hours are recognized for every thousand words; and for papers published in municipal-level journals, 3 academic hours are recognized for every thousand words.
(9) Participation in public training sessions organized by engineering cost consulting enterprises that have been approved or authorized by the China National Construction Cost Association, provincial-level management authorities, and provincial cost associations (excluding general corporate management and skills training) is eligible for credit. Four hours of study can be recognized for each half-day of attendance, with a maximum of 30 hours of credit recognized per year.
Cost Engineer Online Continuing Education Learning Process
Once the registration fee is received by the registration authority, the student’s account is activated immediately. The cost engineer can then log in to the online education platform using their username and password to begin their studies.
Students learn by accessing on-demand course materials, asking questions for answers, and participating in online discussions.
If you forget your password and encounter an error stating that the username or password is incorrect when trying to log in, preventing you from accessing the learning materials, please contact the registration institution you are affiliated with. The registration institution can assist you in changing your password (but not your username). Once you have received the new password, you can log in again using it.
