Education News: Beijing reduces the proportion of students with special talents entering junior high schools in 2016 – Xinhua Net
On the 21st and 22nd, the assessment for students with special talents entering junior high schools in Beijing was organized and implemented uniformly by the education commissions of each district.
This year, all districts in Beijing have reduced the proportion of students admitted based on their special talents, making the competition for these spots even more intense.
Taking Dongcheng District as an example, this year the proportion of students with special talents entering junior high schools from primary schools in this district does not exceed 5% of the total number of enrollment places in the district. The planned number of enrollments is 380 students, and the proportion of students who actually attend school does not exceed 10% of the school’s enrollment plan.
Any student with exceptional skills in sports, arts, or technology who registers online is eligible to participate in the special talent recruitment assessment.
To facilitate students in taking the examinations nearby, Dongcheng District has continued with the examination arrangement from last year, setting up 1 to 2 examination locations in each school district, for a total of 13 examination locations.
The examination venues are divided according to the examination regions, and the time periods are determined on an hourly basis. On the day of the exam, students will enter the designated examination venues in each region at the specified times to take the tests.
On May 23rd, the District Education Admissions and Examinations Center published the list of students who passed the assessment online. Students can check their assessment results on the website.
