The reserves of the naked carp in Qinghai Lake have increased by 0.71 million tons this year – Xinhua News Agency
Xinhua News Agency, Xining, December 11 (Reporters Luo Xiaofei, Zhang Hongxiang) Reporters learned from the Qinghai Provincial Department of Agriculture and Rural Affairs that the latest monitoring results show that the reserves of the naked carp in Qinghai Lake have increased by 7,100 tons this year compared to last year, reaching 108,500 tons. This represents a cumulative increase of more than 40 times since the initial protection measures were implemented in 2002.
The Qinghai Lake naked carp, commonly known as the “Huang fish,” is a unique and precious species found only in Qinghai Lake. It plays a crucial role in maintaining the safety of the “water-fish-bird” ecological chain and biodiversity within the Qinghai Lake basin.
In the 1960s and 1970s, due to factors such as extensive human hunting and the deteriorating environmental conditions in the areas where the Qaidam fish reproduce, the population of the Qaidam fish in Qinghai Lake declined sharply. By 2002, the reserves of this fish species in Qinghai Lake had dwindled to only 2,592 tons.
In 2004, the Qinghai Lake naked carp was listed as an endangered species in the “China Species Red List”.
Since 2003, Qinghai Province has implemented a policy of closing lakes to promote fish reproduction. No entity, collective, or individual is allowed to fish for the naked carp in Qinghai Lake and its main rivers and tributaries, nor are the sale of naked carp or their products permitted.
Meanwhile, efforts to protect the resources of Qinghai Lake have been continuously intensified through measures such as artificial propagation and release of fish, cleaning the river channels that feed into the lake, and designing scientifically sound “fish passages.” As a result, the stock of naked carp in Qinghai Lake has been increasing year by year.
Yang Lin, the deputy director of the Qinghai Provincial Department of Agriculture and Rural Affairs, introduced that as of now, nearly 180 million artificially propagated and released Qingshai Lake naked carps have been introduced into the lake, contributing more than 23% to the recovery of the Qingshai Lake naked carp population.
The Sanjiangyuan area in Qinghai is an important ecological barrier and water conservation region for both China and Asia. Qinghai Lake serves as a natural barrier that prevents the desertification in the west from spreading eastward, as well as an area with significant ecological functions.
In order to protect the ecological environment of the Sanjiangyuan region and the Qinghai Lake area, as well as aquatic wildlife, and to maintain the biodiversity of the Qinghai-Tibet Plateau, Qinghai has issued notices banning fishing in key waters of the Yangtze River, Yellow River, and Qinghai Lake since the beginning of this year. This has led to the establishment of a comprehensive fishing ban management system for each river and lake.
