The cover plate on the microfluidic chip is made of PC material; please do not use solvents that can react chemically with PC.
Do not use a syringe to inject the sample directly onto the chip, as this can easily lead to liquid leakage.
Microfluidic chips with ordinary substrates are tested with pure water at an injection pressure of 500 mbar (for channel depths of 100 μm) or 300 mbar (for channel depths of 50 μm) before shipment.
The chips with glass substrates are tested with pure water at an injection pressure of 800 mbar (for 100 μm channels) before shipment. Please be careful not to collide the chips with sharp objects during use, as this may damage the substrate.
During use, please take into account the viscosity of the solution and do not exceed this range, as it may cause leakage.
For microfluidic microchips with a common substrate, when using a syringe pump for pure water injection, we recommend setting the flow rate below 150 ul/min. For the oil phase, we suggest setting the flow rate below 50 ul/min.
Consider the actual viscosity of the liquid being injected, and gradually increase the value of your flow rate parameter from slow to fast.
After completing the experiments with the general-purpose chip, make sure to clean the internal channels promptly to prevent blockages.
Microfluidic chips are considered consumables and cannot be reused repeatedly for an extended period of time.
No refunds or exchanges will be provided if the chip is damaged due to long-term use or improper handling.
If you need a microfluidic chip that can withstand higher pressures or flow rates, please contact customer service for customization.
