But to be realistic, the right has played a positive role in the process of social progress.
In terms of ending the Cultural Revolution, establishing criteria for determining truth, developing the economy, advancing science and technology, as well as promoting the institutionalization of administrative systems and the protection of human rights, the positive contributions of the right-wing should not be denied.
Thirdly, as for me, although I do not completely agree with some of Li Weidong’s statements, I take his views seriously and respect him as a person. He is sincere; he is serious about China and also takes a serious approach to China’s social issues.
However, I oppose his anti-communist theories. I believe that counter-revolution is unnecessary; revolutions inevitably lead to social unrest, harm to people's livelihoods, and a situation where political groups are mixed with the good and the bad. Moreover, foreign countries may take advantage of such weaknesses to gain influence.
IV. To change or improve China, one must have patience and a sense of responsibility towards the country and its people. Those who attempt political opportunism, seeking to profit from difficult situations, are not on the right side; they are simply scoundrels.
