Damei 360 integrates home decoration features.
Address: 12th Floor, Xingfu Jiayuan, No. 156, Huancheng South Road
It all started with a friend’s recommendation; out of trust, I decided to give it a try. My initial budget was 70,000 yuan for basic renovations.
As soon as they enter the store, a series of scams begin.
This was my first time visiting the store. I just showed them my house layout plan, and they didn’t even measure the actual property itself. Yet, they were able to give me a quote, stating that they could sell my 135-square-meter house for 70,000 yuan. They briefly showed me some of the materials they would use, but I didn’t even know what brand those materials were.
Their second trick is that as soon as you enter the store, they’ll try to persuade you to pay the deposit. Once you pay that money, you’ll never be able to get it back, unless you have enough experience to argue with them effectively.
While I was hesitating about whether to pay the deposit, they would invite their so-called manager to tell you how much discount you could get if you paid the deposit today.
This is a huge scam; I’m a living example of someone who was deceived. In a moment of impulse, I paid a deposit of over ten thousand yuan.
The quote he gave me has many issues: The amount of 70,000 does not include the costs for renovating the plumbing and electricity systems, nor does it cover any doors, cabinets, or the bathroom. These three aspects are actually the major components of the basic installation costs.
Apart from these issues, the fees they charge for their service points are also higher than those of other companies.
I have lost trust in this company; they didn’t explain anything clearly to me before asking me to sign the contract.
When I went to ask them for a refund, they seemed very experienced; there was even a dedicated team assigned to deal with such situations.
Anyway, they’ll insist that it’s the customer’s problem and that they are completely blameless.
There are all sorts of excuses for shirking responsibility, as well as many other details I don’t want to mention; mentioning them would just make me cry. In short, don’t choose them. My friend’s house, which they renovated for her, also turned out to be of poor quality, and they later tried to charge her various extra fees.
What a rip-off! Those were originally just fake, misleading decorations meant to deceive people. Now they’ve been “rebranded” as something supposedly beautiful, but it seems the business has gone bankrupt again, and they’ve changed the design yet again.
So everyone, please don’t choose such a unreliable and deceptive renovation company.
In the future, when making choices, everyone should do more research by using Baidu to look up relevant information and seek advice. After all, home renovation is not a small investment.
