From the past to the present, I have always opposed any form of slander and abuse, and I cannot tolerate such personal attacks at all.
In civilized societies, we should be able to tolerate everything, but we must put an end to such villains.
If we set aside political parties and factions, the first thing we need to resist is this uncivilized behavior.
Since you first sent a request to add me as a friend on Facebook, followed by making sarcastic posts, and then attempting to post the location of what you call my home and my father’s name on social media, I have chosen to remain unresponsive.
Later on, you not only continued to tag me even more frequently than before (six times a day), but also went on to discuss me in rather explicit and humiliating ways on Facebook with your so-called friends. Comments about my appearance, body, fertility, and even things like “planting strawberries in bed” or whether I should use certain devices during intercourse… Well, I’ll just let it go.
Later on, I received messages from several friends regarding a photo of you uploaded to your Facebook profile, along with comments that contained elements of sexual harassment.
I’m sorry, but as a woman, I can no longer remain silent.
After the news about my police report was uploaded, you didn’t show any sign of changing your behavior at all; instead, you became even more arrogant.
I don’t care what your political background is, or what your social status is; in our society, it is necessary for both genders to be respected.
Yes, you can continue with these sarcastic, subtle, humiliating, and abusive remarks. You can also keep saying that you just have good intentions and are concerned about me. You can continue to believe that this isn’t harassment, and you might even deny that the images were made by you or continue to make any other offensive statements.
That’s right; I can’t, and I don’t have the ability to stop you.
I don’t know you, and I don’t want to know you. Moreover, there’s no need for you to comment on my appearance or figure.
I don’t even think there would be a single girl who would agree to let someone humiliate her in such a way just to gain fame.
A friend asked me if I was okay.
Even if I say yes, you wouldn’t believe it.
I don’t think there would be a single girl who, after being bullied in such a way, could still say she’s okay.
Whether in the workplace, society, politics, or business, only those who lack even basic morals would choose to harm any woman in such a manner.
I believe that fairness lies within everyone’s heart.
I’ve excerpted some of the comments for everyone to review and discuss.
The posts you posted yourself should be such that no one could impersonate you, right?
All I can say is that you are the public enemy of civilization.
A knowing smile
Vietnam People’s Daily Online – Vietnamese Prime Minister Phan Minh Chinh attended the third Vietnam National Digital Technology Enterprises Development Forum
During the Third Vietnam National Digital Technology Enterprises Development Forum, two main conferences were held. The discussions centered around two key themes: the role of digital technology enterprises in the country's digital transformation, and their contribution to economic recovery and development both during and after the COVID-19 pandemic.
Minister of Communications and Media, Nguyen Meng Hung, stated that in 2021, despite the ongoing spread of the COVID-19 pandemic, the number of digital technology companies in Vietnam and their revenue continued to grow, with an increase of nearly 10%.
In 2021, the number of digital products in Vietnam increased significantly, focusing on solving major challenges the country faced. Many of these digital products have gone global, and Vietnam’s ranking in digital technology has improved.
Minister Nguyen Mengxiong called on digital technology companies to take responsibility for developing the country’s digital transformation platforms. Undertaking the task of developing these national digital platforms is tantamount to fulfilling a national mission.
At the forum, leaders from various departments and state agencies, as well as enterprises, organizations, and individuals engaged in the research, development, application, and transfer of digital technologies, shared innovative ideas and solutions for mobilizing and pooling resources from across society to support the growth of Vietnamese technology companies and jointly drive the country’s digital transformation. These efforts also aim to facilitate economic recovery after the pandemic.
During his speech at the forum, Prime Minister Fan Mingzheng emphasized that digital transformation is an inevitable path for the world and an objective requirement for development.
Digital transformation has become a global issue that benefits everyone. Therefore, it is essential to mobilize the entire population to participate in this process.
People and businesses are the core, main entities, goals, and driving forces of digital transformation.
Therefore, all policies must be aimed at serving the people and businesses.
Prime Minister Fan Mingzheng emphasized that digital transformation must reflect the national spirit and should be driven primarily by internal forces, with strategy, long-term vision, and decisive actions as key factors. External influences, however, can serve as important catalysts and breakthrough points in this process.
He also believes that digital transformation should drive both in-depth development and sustainable development. It should contribute to the prevention and control of the COVID-19 pandemic, economic recovery and growth, adaptation to subsequent changes, and the overcoming of natural resource depletion. Furthermore, it should support a green transition and the development of renewable energy sources.
Digital transformation requires the participation in the establishment of databases that protect and promote a country's cultural values, historical traditions, and local customs. This effort should also drive the digital transformation of sectors such as banking, taxation, land management and development, as well as logistics.
The ultimate goal of the digital transformation is to make people happier and ensure the continuous prosperity and development of the nation.
Prime Minister Fan Mingzheng has called on governments at all levels, various agencies, and enterprises to increase their leadership and guidance in the development of digital technologies. It is essential to raise awareness of the importance of digital transformation, continue to establish and improve the frameworks related to digital transformation, and enhance national governance. Moreover, efforts should be made to promote the growth of digital technology companies with a spirit of respect, communication, active engagement, and proactivity.
During the forum, Prime Minister Pham Minh Chinh attended the award ceremony for the 2021 “Made in Vietnam” Outstanding Digital Products and the opening ceremony of the “Made in Vietnam” Digital Products Exhibition.
