“The Intelligence Gathering in Xiaoxiang” 2021 China International Rail Transit and Equipment Manufacturing Industry Talent Summit opens – Rolling News – Hunan Daily Online – Huasheng Online
Hunan Daily, December 10th (All-media reporter Zhou Zhiheng) On the 9th, the “Intelligent Talent Summit for China’s International Rail Transit and Equipment Manufacturing Industry – ZhixiaoXiang 2021” opened in Zhuzhou.
Wang Cheng, a member of the Standing Committee of the Provincial Party Committee and head of the Provincial Party Committee Organization Department, attended the launch ceremony and delivered a speech.
Wang Cheng pointed out that hosting a talent summit is an important measure to implement the spirit of the Central Talent Work Conference and the 12th Provincial Party Congress, demonstrating Hunan’s sincere commitment to valuing, seeking, and making effective use of talent.
Hunan has a fine tradition of recognizing, valuing, and respecting talent; it offers extensive platforms to support the development of talents, as well as favorable environmental conditions for achieving a better quality of life. In recent years, the province has actively implemented a talent-led development strategy. Guided by the Furong Talent Action Plan, it has established a comprehensive framework for attracting, nurturing, retaining, and utilizing talents. As a result, Hunan has become a fertile ground for talent growth and achievement, a hotbed for innovation and entrepreneurship, and a pleasant place to live and work.
Currently, Hunan is fully implementing the strategic positioning and mission of “Three Highs and Four New Developments.” It will further broaden its efforts to attract talented individuals, introduce more favorable policies for talent innovation and entrepreneurship, concentrate more resources, and create better conditions. Hunan looks forward to outstanding talents from all sectors joining together to contribute their wisdom and efforts to the province’s high-quality development.
The event site featured exhibition halls for Changsha, Zhuzhou, Xiangtan, as well as the Hunan Free Trade Pilot Zone. The Provincial Department of Science and Technology, the Provincial Department of Industry and Information Technology, and the Provincial Department of Human Resources and Social Security released key lists of technological innovation needs in the advanced manufacturing sector, a directory of talent requirements for the intelligent manufacturing industry, and a directory of talent needs for young professionals in the intelligent manufacturing industry at postdoctoral research stations.
Forty-eight large enterprises, including CRRC (China Railway Corporation), Zoomlion, and Yuanda Technology, recruited talents on-site. Nearly a thousand recent graduates from relevant fields and professionals from the community participated in the talent matchmaking programs.
